 COVID19: FG Publishes 100 Suspended Passports Of Travelers The Federal Government has posted the passport numbers of 100 travelers, who resisted to partake in the compulsory COVID-19 test after they got back into Nigeria. On December 23, the Presidential Task Force on COVID-19 declared that the passports of such people would be suspended. The passports have been suspended as announced by the PTF. The restrictions are taking effect from January 1, 2021 to June 30, 2021. All those who have their passport numbers in the picture below would not be allowed to move outside the boundaries of Nigeria. This update came in on January 2 in a statement from the PTF. It reads; “Based on Presidental authority, travel restrictions are placed on the following passports due to non-compliance to the mandatory Day 7 post-arrival COVID-19 test,” See the list of the defaulting passengers below  The PTF has placed travel restrictions on the first 100 passengers for non-compliance to the mandatory Day 7 post-arrival COVID-19 test.#TakeResponsibility pic.twitter.com/1X4M0Ka8MP — Covid-19 Presidential Task Force (PTF) | Nigeria (@DigiCommsNG) January 3, 2021